            ['title' => 'The Adhan: Listening and Responding',      'emoji' => '📢', 'age_tier' => 'preschool', 'subject' => 'islamic_studies', 'age_min' => 3, 'age_max' => 5, 'is_free' => true,  'duration' => 8,  'activity_type' => 'real_world',  'skill' => 'Islamic daily habit: responding to Adhan', 'description' => 'When the Adhan is heard, stop what you are doing, listen, and repeat each phrase after the caller. Responding to the Adhan — stopping activity, repeating the words, and making dua afterward — trains the automatic Islamic orientation to daily time that structures the Muslim life rhythm through five daily anchors.'],
